: Cumulative basal layer clone size distribution, 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{n}(t)$
\end_inset

, as a function of size (number of cells) rescaled by the average for each
 time point, 
\begin_inset Formula $n/\langle n(t)\rangle$
\end_inset

 as in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "fig:oes-basal-scaling"

\end_inset

, i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{n}(t)$
\end_inset

 denotes the probability of finding a clone with a size equal to, or larger
 than, 
\begin_inset Formula $n/\langle n(t)\rangle$
\end_inset

.
