 sample size, indicating approximately one standard deviation (
\begin_inset Formula $68\%$
\end_inset

).
 In the long time limit, the model predicts that the distribution should
 tend to a simple exponential, 
\begin_inset Formula $\exp\left(-n/\langle n(t)\rangle\right)$
\end_inset

, (black line).
 The model shows good agreement with the experimental data at both short
 and long time points.
